-

Imagine if Tesla built Drones…

@verticalmag How far can electric aircraft actually fly? Well, @joby_aviation has now demonstrated over 150 miles (240 km) on a single charge with its electric vertical take-off and landing (eVTOL) prototype, showing that it’s capable of practical missions using today’s battery technology. For full details about the July 21 flight, visit our sister publication eVTOL.com — and follow @evtolmag for more #eVTOL news!
